  "text": "Another special property of Shapley value for a fair payoff allocation is monotonicity [CITATION_1] . This states that if we change a game such that the contributions of a player to all coalitions stays the same or increases then the final payoff for that player should not decrease. [CITATION_2] also shows that the Shapley value can be described simply by the three properties of efficiency, symmetry, and monotonicity for all cooperative games.",
